statement.p:
The first step for solving each equation below is incorrect. Replace it with the correct step.



6(5^{3t})=20

\log {(6(5^{3t}))}=\log {20}


t \log 8 = \log{53}

t = \log {\dfrac{53}{8}}


12(10)^{-0.06t} = 192

120^{-0.06t} = 192


\log x +\log {(x-2)} = 3

x + (x-2) = 10^3

solution.p:
First, we divide both sides by C to isolate the power.
		b^{kt} = \dfrac{P}{C}
Then we write the exponential equation in logarithmic form:
		 kt \amp = \log_b {\dfrac{P}{C}} \amp\amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by}~k.}
			t  \amp = \dfrac{1}{k}\log_b {\dfrac{P}{C}}
